Local Dev:
1. Install sbt:
https://github.com/harrah/xsbt/wiki/Getting-Started-Setup
2. Use sbt to run the project
3. Go to http://127.0.0.1:8099/assets/demo.html to view demo

Deployment:
1. Run sbt, in sbt console run assembly. This will generate an assemblied jar file in target folder.
2. Run the jar file, e.g. run.sh
3. Run crontab confile to add crontab task.
4. Run Online to do online data processing(only one time executed is enough)

Note:
1. Create conf/app-local.conf for local env configuration

We use Cascel as Cassandra client, it's on Github:
https://github.com/zyeming/cascal